        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 4:44PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mountain Lake, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Pembroke...
Union...
Newport...
Mountain Lake...
Laurel Branch...
and Eggleston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
